1
00:00:01,807 --> 00:00:03,085
Comes fully equipped.

2
00:00:05,757 --> 00:00:07,506
I'm telling you,
it's a steal at $400.

3
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:14,555
- Gotta check with your husband?
- It's just me.

4
00:00:15,624 --> 00:00:16,349
Mommy?

5
00:00:17,601 --> 00:00:21,062
- Can I have a quarter for the machine?
- Honey, I said wait for me by the pool.

6
00:00:22,231 --> 00:00:23,856
I thought you said it was "just me."

7
00:00:24,563 --> 00:00:27,902
I meant my husband's out of the picture.
It's just me and my son.

8
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:30,404
The other tenants don't like noise.

9
00:00:30,573 --> 00:00:31,614
He's very quiet.

10
00:00:32,657 --> 00:00:34,158
I'm gonna need two months up front.

11
00:00:36,878 --> 00:00:37,978
Here, honey.

12
00:00:41,751 --> 00:00:44,101
Hey, no running.
You hear me, Miles?

13
00:01:38,043 --> 00:01:39,056
Mom!

14
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:40,307
Mommy! Help!

15
00:01:45,924 --> 00:01:46,924
Miles?

16
00:01:47,546 --> 00:01:49,734
- Miles, what happened?
- Mommy!

17
00:01:52,855 --> 00:01:53,855
God.

18
00:01:54,114 --> 00:01:55,164
Mr. Vonner.

19
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:02,580
- What were you doing in here?
- He was all alone.

20
00:02:02,923 --> 00:02:04,081
He was scared.

21
00:02:04,249 --> 00:02:07,334
His chest hurt.
He kept calling out for Kimberly.

22
00:02:07,503 --> 00:02:08,503
Kimberly?

23
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:10,087
That's his wife.

24
00:02:11,421 --> 00:02:14,425
She died last year.
Now how would you know that?

25
00:02:14,594 --> 00:02:17,386
- I heard him.
- What are you talking about?

26
00:02:18,621 --> 00:02:20,890
He's still talking right now.

27
00:02:22,174 --> 00:02:23,174
Honey...

28
00:02:25,235 --> 00:02:26,061
He's dead.

29
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:29,633
I told you! I can hear him!

30
00:02:30,109 --> 00:02:31,359
I can hear him!

31
00:02:32,359 --> 00:02:34,547
<i>Miles, you there? Pick up.</i>

32
00:02:35,737 --> 00:02:36,906
Where are you?

33
00:02:37,298 --> 00:02:39,742
I'll fill you in later.
I need you to take care of something.

34
00:02:39,911 --> 00:02:41,787
- <i>Like what?</i>
- The security tapes

35
00:02:41,912 --> 00:02:45,164
from the pylon camera feeds.
They need to accidentally get erased.

36
00:02:45,735 --> 00:02:46,835
Erased? Why?

37
00:02:47,171 --> 00:02:49,483
I ain't got time for questions.
Just do it.

38
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:51,587
Which ones?

39
00:02:52,069 --> 00:02:53,214
Look on your monitors.

40
00:02:57,309 --> 00:02:58,359
<i>You see us?</i>

41
00:03:01,307 --> 00:03:04,183
Yeah. You're on number 4.
Is that Kate?

42
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:05,935
<i>What are you doing out there?</i>

43
00:03:06,104 --> 00:03:09,024
Just erase number 4.
And if anyone asks, I'm off the grid.

44
00:03:09,149 --> 00:03:12,233
- I'm looking for the escaped hostile.
- You mean your pal Sayid?

45
00:03:12,834 --> 00:03:14,485
You gonna help me or not?!

46
00:03:15,396 --> 00:03:18,405
- Yeah, yeah. I got it.
- <i>All right. I owe you one.</i>

47
00:03:19,274 --> 00:03:20,825
You go back and and find Juliet,

48
00:03:20,994 --> 00:03:22,952
see if anyone's noticed yet
if Ben's gone missin'.

49
00:03:23,398 --> 00:03:25,711
What are you gonna do
when they find out?

50
00:03:25,836 --> 00:03:27,414
Do my best to cover it up.

51
00:03:27,583 --> 00:03:30,042
In case you haven't noticed,
I'm the head of security.

52
00:03:31,961 --> 00:03:33,661
I'll see you back there.

53
00:03:39,458 --> 00:03:40,758
Where's Lafleur?

54
00:03:41,457 --> 00:03:43,958
He's out looking for
the escaped prisoner.

55
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:46,308
I tried to get him on his walkie,
but...

56
00:03:47,209 --> 00:03:48,519
He must be out of range.

57
00:03:49,147 --> 00:03:50,147
Damn it.

58
00:03:50,356 --> 00:03:53,065
All right.
Then it's gonna have to be you.

59
00:03:53,849 --> 00:03:55,317
Jim already knows about this,

60
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:57,820
but I'm gonna bring you
into the circle of trust.

61
00:03:59,207 --> 00:04:00,857
Can I trust you, Miles?

62
00:04:01,335 --> 00:04:02,366
Absolutely.

63
00:04:02,534 --> 00:04:03,409
Okay. Good.

64
00:04:04,961 --> 00:04:08,634
I need you to take this out
to Radzinsky at grid 3-3-4.

65
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:11,204
He'll give you something in return.

66
00:04:11,329 --> 00:04:14,461
I want you to bring it back to me
with no questions asked.

67
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:16,380
Understood?

68
00:04:21,085 --> 00:04:22,678
We're not supposed to be in 3-3-4.

69
00:04:24,723 --> 00:04:26,056
Isn't that hostile territory?

70
00:04:26,834 --> 00:04:28,809
Welcome to the circle of trust.

71
00:04:42,608 --> 00:04:43,958
Stop right there!

72
00:04:47,077 --> 00:04:49,085
What are you doing here?
I was expecting Lafleur.

73
00:04:50,608 --> 00:04:53,000
Lafleur's busy.
Horace sent me instead.

74
00:04:54,517 --> 00:04:56,573
- I'm in the circle of trust.
- Get out.

75
00:05:04,544 --> 00:05:06,544
I'm supposed to give you this.

76
00:05:06,828 --> 00:05:08,474
And he said
you had something for me.

77
00:05:29,606 --> 00:05:31,107
What happened to him?

78
00:05:31,232 --> 00:05:32,682
He had an accident.

79
00:05:35,283 --> 00:05:37,586
- What kind of accident?
- He fell into a ditch.

80
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:40,172
Is that a bullet hole in his head?

81
00:05:41,670 --> 00:05:44,134
- The ditch had a gun?
- It doesn't matter what happened

82
00:05:44,571 --> 00:05:48,555
because knowing that is not your job.
Your job is to do what I tell you to.

83
00:06:04,370 --> 00:06:06,620
Take him back to Horace now, Miles.

84
00:06:31,293 --> 00:06:32,293
Okay...

85
00:06:34,855 --> 00:06:36,478
So what really happened?

86
00:06:39,342 --> 00:06:52,161
Subtitle:
www.sub-way.fr (1.00)

87
00:06:59,547 --> 00:07:00,947
I need to see her.

88
00:07:24,958 --> 00:07:25,694
Ma?

89
00:07:29,710 --> 00:07:30,710
It's me.

90
00:07:39,646 --> 00:07:40,646
Miles.

91
00:07:41,709 --> 00:07:43,059
I'm sorry that...

92
00:07:44,645 --> 00:07:46,595
I couldn't make it by sooner.

93
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:47,833
It's okay.

94
00:07:48,523 --> 00:07:49,823
You're here now.

95
00:07:54,646 --> 00:07:56,827
Why did you come, Miles?

96
00:07:59,271 --> 00:08:00,821
I need you to tell me

97
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:03,614
why I'm this way...

98
00:08:08,006 --> 00:08:10,141
How I do the things I do.

99
00:08:13,645 --> 00:08:15,134
And I need to know why

100
00:08:15,259 --> 00:08:17,287
you won't talk to me
about my father.

101
00:08:18,398 --> 00:08:20,374
Because he never cared about us...

102
00:08:22,503 --> 00:08:24,103
Never cared about you.

103
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:26,130
I need to know where he is.

104
00:08:26,583 --> 00:08:29,007
- It doesn't matter where.
- It does matter.

105
00:08:30,093 --> 00:08:31,760
- I have a right to know!
- He's dead.

106
00:08:36,976 --> 00:08:38,176
Your father...

107
00:08:39,976 --> 00:08:42,729
Kicked us out
when you were just a baby.

108
00:08:45,101 --> 00:08:47,317
He didn't want anything
to do with us.

109
00:08:48,601 --> 00:08:51,196
So the less you knew about him,

110
00:08:51,802 --> 00:08:52,727
the better.

111
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,165
Why didn't you just tell me?

112
00:08:59,290 --> 00:09:00,790
Because it was over.

113
00:09:02,626 --> 00:09:04,876
Your dad has been dead

114
00:09:05,225 --> 00:09:06,795
a long time.

115
00:09:12,476 --> 00:09:13,826
Where's his body?

116
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:19,850
Somewhere you can never go.

117
00:09:26,976 --> 00:09:30,027
Pierre, if it was caused
by the electromagnetism, we must know.

118
00:09:30,788 --> 00:09:32,154
You wanna see it now?

119
00:09:32,412 --> 00:09:33,488
He just got back.

120
00:09:34,101 --> 00:09:35,866
I'll send him out with it
right away.

121
00:09:39,601 --> 00:09:40,996
Did you bring the package?

122
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,915
"Package"?
You mean the corpse?

123
00:09:43,084 --> 00:09:46,543
Yeah. Now I need you to bring it out
to Dr. Chang at the Orchid.

124
00:09:51,175 --> 00:09:53,199
Listen, man. I'm security.

125
00:09:53,663 --> 00:09:56,845
If you need somebody to drive the van,
can't someone from the motor pool do it?

126
00:09:57,014 --> 00:10:00,037
If I wanted someone from the motor pool,
I would have asked them.

127
00:10:00,162 --> 00:10:03,393
And since Lafleur decided to disappear,
you're all I've got.

128
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:07,481
So just bring it out to Dr. Chang,
and we'll all call it a day.

129
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,960
What the hell are you doing?!
That's my van!

130
00:10:22,085 --> 00:10:23,372
Nah, I just signed it out.

131
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:24,915
Doesn't matter. It's mine.

132
00:10:25,084 --> 00:10:27,116
- Well, where you going?
- The Orchid.

133
00:10:27,241 --> 00:10:29,962
Me too. I made lunch
for the crew. Sandwiches.

134
00:10:30,243 --> 00:10:32,965
Want one? Ham and cheese,
and I made my secret garlic mayo.

135
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:36,051
You'll wait for the next van.

136
00:10:36,220 --> 00:10:38,345
We're going to the same place.
Why don't we carpool?

137
00:10:38,514 --> 00:10:40,722
It'll help with global warming,
which hasn't happened yet,

138
00:10:40,890 --> 00:10:42,474
so maybe we can prevent it.

139
00:10:43,857 --> 00:10:46,478
Wait a sec.
Are you on some kind of secret mission?

140
00:10:46,994 --> 00:10:48,094
Just get in.

141
00:11:00,306 --> 00:11:01,406
How'd it go?

142
00:11:01,743 --> 00:11:03,930
We gave him to the Others.

143
00:11:04,055 --> 00:11:06,373
- Anyone see you?
- I don't think so.

144
00:11:06,992 --> 00:11:08,242
Did James help?

145
00:11:08,556 --> 00:11:10,711
Yes. Thank you so much
for sending him.

146
00:11:11,431 --> 00:11:12,431
Of course.

147
00:11:15,129 --> 00:11:17,129
I got here as soon as I could.

148
00:11:17,993 --> 00:11:20,543
All the vans were out,
so I had to ru...

149
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:24,808
Where's Ben?

150
00:11:28,129 --> 00:11:29,129
Did he...

151
00:11:31,006 --> 00:11:33,367
- Then where is he?
- Roger, I'm so sorry.

152
00:11:33,492 --> 00:11:35,777
I was gone for ten minutes.
I don't know.

153
00:11:35,992 --> 00:11:38,613
What? You said he was dying.
How could he be gone?

154
00:11:38,782 --> 00:11:41,950
What is she telling me,
that he just got up and walked out?

155
00:11:42,300 --> 00:11:43,869
You're supposed to watch him!

156
00:11:44,447 --> 00:11:47,122
- I know. Roger, if we just calm down-
- Don't tell me to calm down!

157
00:11:47,803 --> 00:11:49,541
Somebody came and took my boy?!

158
00:11:49,710 --> 00:11:51,001
I know. I am so sorry.

159
00:11:51,243 --> 00:11:52,843
I'm going to security.

160
00:12:00,431 --> 00:12:01,431
Well...

161
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:04,681
Here we go.

162
00:12:20,220 --> 00:12:21,887
How do you spell "bounty hunter"?

163
00:12:22,012 --> 00:12:24,562
What are you doing,
writing your memoirs?

164
00:12:24,764 --> 00:12:25,964
It's personal.

165
00:12:35,574 --> 00:12:36,574
Dude...

166
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,167
Did you just... You know?

167
00:12:40,387 --> 00:12:41,387
What?

168
00:12:41,513 --> 00:12:42,513
You know.

169
00:12:43,532 --> 00:12:44,679
It stinks. Did you...

170
00:12:46,449 --> 00:12:47,899
Well, it wasn't me.

171
00:12:48,888 --> 00:12:50,638
So roll down your window.

172
00:12:53,823 --> 00:12:55,732
Nah, man,
there's something foul in here.

173
00:12:56,182 --> 00:12:58,985
- It's coming from back there.
- Maybe it's your famous garlic mayo.

174
00:12:59,154 --> 00:13:00,654
That's not possible.

175
00:13:02,389 --> 00:13:04,699
Okay, maybe it is possible.
Pull over. I gotta check.

176
00:13:04,867 --> 00:13:06,451
Forget it.
You're imagining things.

177
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:09,496
I gotta check. If those sandwiches
are bad, people could get sick.

178
00:13:11,374 --> 00:13:12,874
Will you pull over?!

179
00:13:36,131 --> 00:13:39,151
There's a body bag back here.
There's a body in it.

180
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,445
That's traditionally
what you put in a body bag.

181
00:13:41,614 --> 00:13:42,904
Who is he? What happened?

182
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:47,600
Don't worry about it
and don't tell anybody you saw him.

183
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,760
Dude, what happened to him?

184
00:13:50,978 --> 00:13:52,372
His name's Alvarez.

185
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:56,341
He was digging a hole and thinking
about some chick named Andr?a.

186
00:13:57,392 --> 00:14:00,042
Then he felt this sharp pain
in his mouth,

187
00:14:00,167 --> 00:14:02,370
which turned out to be
a filling from his tooth

188
00:14:02,495 --> 00:14:04,885
being yanked right out
of its socket and...

189
00:14:05,456 --> 00:14:06,970
Blowing through his brain.

190
00:14:08,144 --> 00:14:09,494
Then he was dead.

191
00:14:10,408 --> 00:14:12,642
How does a filling get blown
through someone's head?

192
00:14:13,579 --> 00:14:15,179
Got me. Can we go now?

193
00:14:16,516 --> 00:14:18,266
How do you know all this?

194
00:14:18,455 --> 00:14:19,455
Because...

195
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:22,277
- I know.
- How do you know what he was thinking?

196
00:14:22,954 --> 00:14:24,054
I just know.

197
00:14:25,016 --> 00:14:26,916
You can talk to dead people.

198
00:14:28,831 --> 00:14:30,431
Can we please just go?

199
00:14:32,578 --> 00:14:35,415
Don't worry, dude.
Your secret's safe with me.

200
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:36,708
You wanna know why?

201
00:14:37,828 --> 00:14:39,794
- No.
- 'cause I can talk to 'em, too.

202
00:14:50,766 --> 00:14:54,566
If you don't mind, Mr. Gray,
can you tell me what happened to him?

203
00:14:56,452 --> 00:14:57,813
Last labor day weekend,

204
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,170
drunk driver ran the light.

205
00:15:03,414 --> 00:15:04,528
That was that.

206
00:15:05,292 --> 00:15:07,042
Where is your son buried?

207
00:15:07,641 --> 00:15:11,641
We cremated him, scattered the ashes
on the football field at school.

208
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:16,582
For what I do,
it's much better if there's a body.

209
00:15:18,392 --> 00:15:22,171
But your ad said you could communicate
with the dead anytime, anywhere.

210
00:15:22,766 --> 00:15:25,049
- I know what my ad says, but...
- Please.

211
00:15:28,866 --> 00:15:30,816
I just want you to ask him...

212
00:15:33,586 --> 00:15:35,059
Did he know that I loved him?

213
00:15:38,204 --> 00:15:39,802
It's gonna cost extra.

214
00:15:41,737 --> 00:15:42,737
Of course.

215
00:15:48,517 --> 00:15:49,460
Thank you.

216
00:15:58,035 --> 00:15:59,177
Okay, now...

217
00:16:00,841 --> 00:16:02,513
Please give me your hands.

218
00:16:06,097 --> 00:16:09,489
I want you to concentrate on Russell.
Just get a picture of him in your head.

219
00:16:09,656 --> 00:16:10,878
Can you do that?

220
00:16:11,808 --> 00:16:12,953
Yeah. Okay.

221
00:16:29,925 --> 00:16:31,025
Did it work?

222
00:16:32,820 --> 00:16:35,370
Your son says
he knew that you loved him.

223
00:16:36,684 --> 00:16:37,934
He always knew.

224
00:16:41,075 --> 00:16:42,075
Thank you.

225
00:16:42,767 --> 00:16:44,467
I'm sorry for your loss.

226
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:54,390
Excuse me.

227
00:16:55,517 --> 00:16:56,682
Miles Straume?

228
00:16:57,140 --> 00:16:59,977
- Yeah.
- Hi. My name's Naomi Dorrit.

229
00:17:01,311 --> 00:17:03,751
My employer's been following
your work for some time now,

230
00:17:03,918 --> 00:17:06,859
and he's interested in retaining
your rather unique services.

231
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,410
There's a restaurant
not too far from here.

232
00:17:10,577 --> 00:17:12,663
Would you like to hear
what I have to say?

233
00:17:12,923 --> 00:17:14,444
Yeah. Absolutely.

234
00:17:53,827 --> 00:17:54,698
Hi, Roger.

235
00:17:58,328 --> 00:17:59,279
You okay?

236
00:18:01,203 --> 00:18:02,353
Let me see...

237
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:04,310
Well, my son got shot

238
00:18:04,958 --> 00:18:07,008
and now he's disappeared, so...

239
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:10,214
I think I'm pretty far from okay.

240
00:18:12,285 --> 00:18:13,835
You know, I'm sure...

241
00:18:15,067 --> 00:18:16,867
Things are gonna work out.

242
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:21,743
Well,

243
00:18:22,259 --> 00:18:23,959
thanks for the pep talk.

244
00:18:25,587 --> 00:18:27,648
I just have a feeling
he's gonna be okay.

245
00:18:31,853 --> 00:18:33,654
What do you mean, a feeling?

246
00:18:34,175 --> 00:18:36,824
I just don't think
that you should give up hope.

247
00:18:43,879 --> 00:18:45,479
Do you know something?

248
00:18:47,358 --> 00:18:49,922
- Do you know what happened to my son?
- No, I don't.

249
00:18:50,786 --> 00:18:53,632
Wait a minute.
Why are you so interested in my kid?

250
00:18:54,064 --> 00:18:56,343
I'm sorry I came over here,
I was just trying to help.

251
00:18:56,593 --> 00:18:57,970
You're trying to help, huh?

252
00:18:58,473 --> 00:19:00,023
You wanna help, Kate?

253
00:19:01,062 --> 00:19:03,767
Well, why don't you just mind
your own business?

254
00:19:23,052 --> 00:19:24,913
I don't know
why you just won't admit it.

255
00:19:25,175 --> 00:19:27,124
You can trust me.
I talk to lots of dead people.

256
00:19:27,489 --> 00:19:30,947
So you have conversations with them,
like they're your pals?

257
00:19:31,219 --> 00:19:32,634
