00:36:41,539 --> 00:36:44,451
Got a perfectly good explanation
for what you saw on that tape.

507
00:36:44,619 --> 00:36:45,953
I sure as hell hope so.

508
00:36:50,956 --> 00:36:52,647
- You talk to Horace yet?
- No.

509
00:36:52,772 --> 00:36:55,045
I thought that after 3 years
of working together,

510
00:36:55,214 --> 00:36:57,050
I'd give you
the benefit of the doubt...

511
00:36:59,548 --> 00:37:00,748
Get some rope.

512
00:37:11,445 --> 00:37:12,445
Mr. Gray?

513
00:37:13,155 --> 00:37:15,172
I hope you don't mind.
Your gate was open.

514
00:37:15,297 --> 00:37:17,109
Mr. Straume.
Of course. No problem.

515
00:37:18,886 --> 00:37:20,636
What, what brings you by?

516
00:37:21,579 --> 00:37:22,679
Well, sir...

517
00:37:24,131 --> 00:37:27,131
I'm about to go on a boat trip
for a while,

518
00:37:28,069 --> 00:37:28,871
and...

519
00:37:30,937 --> 00:37:33,137
I wanted to give this back to you.

520
00:37:39,793 --> 00:37:40,993
I lied to you,

521
00:37:41,788 --> 00:37:42,788
Mr. Gray.

522
00:37:43,892 --> 00:37:46,054
I wasn't able to talk to your son.

523
00:37:50,678 --> 00:37:52,519
Why are you telling me this?

524
00:37:53,011 --> 00:37:56,054
You could have just let me
go on believing what you said.

525
00:37:56,609 --> 00:37:58,482
That wouldn't have been fair
to your son.

526
00:37:59,138 --> 00:38:00,027
I'm sorry?

527
00:38:04,353 --> 00:38:07,013
If you needed your son
to know that you loved him,

528
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:09,870
you should've told him
when he was still alive.

529
00:38:39,985 --> 00:38:42,861
Sorry I said you were afraid
to talk toour dad, dude.

530
00:38:43,029 --> 00:38:44,613
Don't worry about it.

531
00:38:46,165 --> 00:38:47,573
I used to hate my dad, too.

532
00:38:47,742 --> 00:38:50,118
- Yeah?
- He left when I was 10.

533
00:38:53,605 --> 00:38:55,402
But the best thing I ever did

534
00:38:55,683 --> 00:38:57,167
was give him a second chance.

535
00:38:58,175 --> 00:39:02,182
We got to be the best of friends,
and although I may never see him again,

536
00:39:03,273 --> 00:39:04,323
I miss him.

537
00:39:05,086 --> 00:39:06,551
And I know he feels the same.

538
00:39:07,544 --> 00:39:10,494
My dad didn't leave when I was 10.
I was a baby.

539
00:39:11,818 --> 00:39:13,168
I never knew him.

540
00:39:14,562 --> 00:39:16,062
And I don't want to.

541
00:39:16,926 --> 00:39:18,376
It's not happening.

542
00:39:19,144 --> 00:39:21,144
That was Luke's attitude, too.

543
00:39:22,546 --> 00:39:24,357
- What?
- In <i>Empire</i>,

544
00:39:25,527 --> 00:39:27,431
Luke found out Wader was his father,

545
00:39:27,556 --> 00:39:30,981
but instead of putting away
his lightsaber and talking about it,

546
00:39:31,106 --> 00:39:33,202
he overreacted
and got his hand cut off.

547
00:39:34,832 --> 00:39:38,041
I mean, they worked it out eventually,
but at what cost?

548
00:39:38,649 --> 00:39:42,101
Another Death Star was destroyed,
Boba Fett got eaten by the Sarlacc,

549
00:39:42,226 --> 00:39:43,776
and we got the Ewoks.

550
00:39:45,178 --> 00:39:47,365
It all could've been avoided
if they'd just,

551
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:49,200
you know, communicated.

552
00:39:50,503 --> 00:39:53,153
And let's face it.
The Ewoks sucked, dude.

553
00:40:54,442 --> 00:40:56,196
Miles? I need you.

554
00:40:58,390 --> 00:40:59,372
You do?

555
00:40:59,845 --> 00:41:02,209
Sub's here from H.Q.
I need your help bringing them in.

556
00:41:02,957 --> 00:41:06,207
- Sure. New recruits?
- No, scientists from Ann Arbor.

557
00:41:06,902 --> 00:41:09,152
Get your van
and let's get to the dock.

558
00:41:23,316 --> 00:41:26,016
- Can I get a hand with this?
- Yeah, sure.

559
00:41:37,661 --> 00:41:38,711
Hey, Miles.

560
00:41:41,490 --> 00:41:42,840
Long time no see.

